\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Would you go out to have a meal with them sometimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Would you go to their homes to have a meal sometimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Well we would have - in there tea and supper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Did you and your husband have any separate friends or were they always friends of all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 No. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 If friends came visiting would you ask them to stay to tea normally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Well yes, I didn't used to have a lot of visitors see. Not those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 The children had their own friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Only when - children grew up, used to have - they'd bring their girl friends then and - sometimes their family would come, we was alway
s friendly with the family as well as the girl. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Would they call casually sometimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Yes. Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 People often say that they made their own amusements in those days. Can you think of any amusements or ways you entertained your
selves or hour friends?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 No, we never used to do nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Play the organ sometimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 And chat? Your home at number nine, did you have the same landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 No. No, was a different landlord, he lived out - Redruth, som
ewhere in Redruth he lived. But - he was a - he was a - bachelor, but he was nice landlord.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Did you see much of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 No, he used to come sometimes for the rent and sometimes used to have three or four months waiting for him. But father used to 
- paint the windows for him of our house or mend the roof if it wanted - sometimes when he come he used - some of the rent was took up in - what we bought for materials. Father always kept up the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 What was his name?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 He was called - Vyvyan.
 He used to appreciate father doing the house a lot. Yes. In fact, when we came out from - we - we got a house belonging to he - up Centenary Road for Doreen, through we being - and then Doreen bought that after.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 He had other houses up there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Who would you have thought were considered the most important people around here in your young married life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Oh we never - I - never thought anybody was - you know, most important, 'cos they were all one level like weren't we those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Except the foundry employers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Oh yes, well they were - nice people and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Do you think most of the working class had the same standard of living or were some a bit better off than others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Well some were better off, some used to get more wages I suppose you see, it all depends what they do.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Which ones normally would get more wages?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 
Well - anyone you know that was - trades people, you know, the mason or a painter, they would get more wages because they had to learn that didn't they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Learn a trade?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Do you remember any families being thought of as rough in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Called? Well, no, I - I don't - I think everybody was the average you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Did you and your husband have a struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 
Oh I did so. You would with fifteen shilling a week wouldn't ee. And I had a lot of unemployment in it you see, the mines closed twice. One - once when they closed - he was out two years and a half. Second time two years. I had - only unemployment - 
shilling a child then. And when I had the last baby - Phyllis, a shilling was cut off and put on the baby, I had to keep - they two for a shilling then. So I never had much money for save nor to gamble with did I. Very hard time - life I've - very hard ti
mes I had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 What was the main difference if he was unemployed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 The main difference? Oh well the mines closed see, and then they - or - a lot of people out then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 That was after the first world war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Yes. Slump it was you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 In the first part of your marriage was he unemployed at all, before the end of the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 No. Only while we had the children small.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 He didn't have to go to the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 No, he couldn't because he was exempted through - producing tin.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Did you ever have to get help from the Guardians? When your husband was unemployed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 When he was employed or unemployed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Unemployed.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Well not very much because we had - those days we had to make our dole do you see. Did have - I remember once having s
omething when I was going to have the last baby, now I don't - I rather think it was - some calico, you know, material like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 That was Dorreen in 1917?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Yes. Yes. Baby.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 That was Leonard, that was after the first world war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Yes, well Len
nie was seven years between she and he, well then I had - to get all new things, I remember what you think I did for buy bit of material and make nightdresses for the baby. Had a rooster up in the crate, we were saving it for Christmas, I had to sell that
 and buy the material. That's our hardships we had. Nothing like it is now today. They've got everything provided now haven't they. I never - before he went. He was no man for begging. No, he'd rather go short.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 When he was unemployed after the first world war he actually had to go before the Board of Guardians to apply for help did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 He - couldn't have any - I had to wait 'til he get work. 'Til he get his money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 But he did go before the Guardians?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Yes, he went work after - there was -
 he was home a long time. Two year - two year one spell and two year and a half another. And then we went back work and you got work - used to have to work they days three weeks and have a fortnights pay, or else work a fortnight and have a weeks pay, tha
t's the way the mine used to run. And when he went back was three weeks. Had to work three weeks to have a fortnights pay.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Did Mr Tresidder do anything towards mending the children shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Yes, always. Yes, used to go up - we had a little house up
 top of the garden, out house, he used to go up there and do them. Had a toe boy, iron toe boy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 And he would be able to put the soles on them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Used to mend them, yes, had to do that because you couldn't afford pay to have them mended.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 He always mended the children}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16214145\charrsid3556460 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 s shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 And yours as well?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Going back to when you were working at the mine, those handcuffs that you described to me, were they like a mitten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Very much, the same. Bind - bind around your hand and only had the thumb showing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 You made those yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Yes, I used to make them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 When you described one process as being self packers, could you tell me what self packing was involved, what actually was a self packer?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Well there w
as - a - a iron going up and hitched to a machinery on the top, and a round - round like a - well a dumbbell I should call it to the bottom, only was all iron, and then they would turn a handle and that would work, and that would come and go to the keeve,
 pack the - work. And then the last upshot - last time they had to go you had to pack with it because it - the packers weren't heavy enough. You see it had to be packed hard you see, for to go in the tin house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 You said that you lived at number nine Mid Centenary Row?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Until your husband died in 1954?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Then I went down to our Phyllis - broke up and went and lived with Phyllis.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 That was still in Camborne was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Yes, down Park Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 That's your married daughter then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 
When you were walking across the Crofty to Tincraft in the mornings with your long sweeping skirts, how did you manage to keep them out of the dust or the mud?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Well we didn't have them quite so long as that, they weren't sweeping, but 
they were long, and we used - managed not to have them - sweeping up the floor. 'Cos that would be at the bottoms out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Some people used to have braid around the bottoms didn't they?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Braid? Yes. Well some - yes, binding, that's right. And then w
e used to have three rows of braid on the skirt of our best ones but not everyday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 You were saying that you had a rooster up in the crate that you had to bring in for your baby clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Did you actually keep chickens?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 No, but this one was going to be special for Christmas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 You didn't normally have them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Yes. No, didn't normally keep fouls, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Nor have any eggs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 That's right, no. Put in - there - there was furnaces, fires, and they would burn night do you see
, that was poison really, arsenic you know, is - well some men used to go out there and have - their noses tied up and mouth see for do that. But that never had nothing to do with me see, they was outside from me altogether. Another part.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 What would they do with it then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Well they send it away see. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 That was white arsenic?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 What was the tin colour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Well the - well the tin was brown see and - that used to be sacked up and sent away to the smelters. Smelt works - smelti
ng works. Well away from us - was nearly black you know, dark, and iron was - very dark brown. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 And they had to treat them all indifferent departments?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Well I could see - I have seen them different you know, the colours, because - I never use
d to work nothing with it, but I've seen the - samples of them. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Do you remember any of your little brothers that died?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 No. I - just - were just two, one - one was eight months old, and the other one was younger than that. Mother couldn't re
ar boys, she had four and they all died. But I didn't remember - didn't know nothing about the other two, because I wasn't old enough see. They were born some of them before I was born. So that we was mixed up you see, I can't remember them all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 You remember the little one that was eight months old?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 
Oh yes, he was - he died in a - we made a bed in two armchairs, you know, we used to they days they did in the kitchen, by the fire, and I remember me seeing he in that there bed, and remember he died
. They all had like declined bowels. She could never rear a boy. She had four and never reared one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 When he was in the two chairs that was when he'd come poorly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Yes, when he was - when he was poorly. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 How old would you have been then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 How old would you have been when this boy that you remember died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Oh well, oh well a little girl going school. A girl going school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Do you remember his funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Yes. I remember - mother - they used to wear capes that day
 women did. Cape. And I remember mother going funeral with a black cape, black hat, used to be all black. And - the little baby had a white coffin. I think it was - buried down Camborne church. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Did any of the children go to the funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 No. Weren't old enough see - to go funeral.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Just mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 
Yes, mother and father went and - some friends I suppose they were you see, but I remember mother with this cape, because I remember the undertaker - she said, oh I can't get up the
se gloves or something, and mother used to go out work they days, and he said, all as you can remember Mary is the scrubbing brush. So she was called Mary see, Elizabeth Mary, so - he said, you don't know nothing about putting up gloves, Mary, all you kno
w
 about is the scrubbing brush. I remember her - she saying Mr Rogers he was called, you used to know Rogers the cabinet maker - down - where Harvey and Co. got the place, well it was his father, they had a carpenters shop up here to the back lane, and - h
e - used to be the undertaker for all the - family. Mm.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 He would have had the funeral of your grandparents as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Yes. See, everybody those days had a - made a funeral, the neighbours. Proper funeral.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 The friends who came, would they be neighbours or any relations of yours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Well, some of them would be see. Be - the neighbours, 'cos we was all very friendly. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 That would be neighbours in your street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Did people come to see the baby laid out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 
Well no, one of the neighbours would come in and - lay the baby out after it died, but - didn't nobody particular come you know not to see it after it was - in the box you know, more than the family like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 The family would?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Was that generally done in those days, once people died did they have friends and relations come to see them in their coffin?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Well - they did used to some people you know but I wasn't old enough hardly to know - what - they did to the - others, but - I expect th
at had to do if you were friendly you know, with the people. But those days they were very good the people were, for friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 They would sort of pay last respects?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 'Cos one neighbour there always came in when my mother - when she was expecting h
er ba - had her baby. Mm, always did, the middle of the night or by day. So they were good you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Did that neighbour normally do that sort of work for anybody or just for your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Well just used 'cos they were very friendly you see, she only lived two doors from we.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Did she come in and have a cup of tea sometimes and have a chat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 And she would - she took to we children you see because she never had not children. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Would that have been a walking funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Well yes - most walking those days see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 And singing on the way did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Well you see - they - couldn't afford cars you know, they - those days things were very hard, the times were hard see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Did the mourners come back to tea afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Well, ye
s, few but not many didn't used to. They understood you see if you could - afford things see. 'Cos even those days things were expensive to what the wages were you know. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 You wouldn't recall what a funeral would cost?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Well, I don't think it w
as - the little box wasn't very heavy I don't think. That wasn't very - much cost, and then you see if we was walking we - just - wasn't so much you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Do you remember any adults funeral from your house or from your mother's house in the old days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 
Well my grandmother - father's mother was buried from our house, she lived there with us, she was eight - over eighty good bit, but - I were a bit old - I were older then but not - didn't go funeral.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Did mother go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Yes, and father. But didn't - 'cos was father's mother you see. Yes. She was buried up Centenary. Mm, got a grave up there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 What about grandpa, was he buried there as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 No, I - don't - I can never - remember anything about him, because he seemed to have - died - whe
n my father was young. See my father was another boy besides father and he went to America, and don't seems as though granny heard anything from him, she only had my father. And he was - she used to go out work and leave he in on his own see. Mm.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 What sort of work did she do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Well used to go to peoples houses you know, cleaning up and - washing and all - see. But - that's how we managed those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 She came to live with you, where was her home before then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Well she did live in a small house here at the back of this row.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 In Camborne?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Yes. Yes, she lived in Camborne.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 And you can just remember her living there and going out to do charring jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 I can - remember her living with we, yes. 'Cos she used to be in the same
 bedroom as we girls, you know, was only two bedrooms, and father and mother had the small bedroom and we children and granny was in the big bedroom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Would that be all the children in the big bedroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Well see - we weren't all - the family that mother had living, there was some died you see and we wasn't a number. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 In this big bedroom where you were with granny?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Well some would sleep with granny see, a big bed, and then another big bed would take the remainder you see. Mm. Then moth
er always had the small one in with her, the baby one. Mm. Used to have manners those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 
I know some people when they had a good many children and just the one bedroom sometimes they would put partitions in that room, with boys one end and girls the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Yes. Yes, well - well we never had no big boys see to do that for, because they died very babies you see and we were all girls. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Another person told me that when they were small they didn't have beds, they used to have a palias}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8526680\charrsid3556460 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460  on the floor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Oh yes, some did, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 You never had that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 No, never had nothing like that. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 You were saying that mother used to go out working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Scrubbing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Did she do this every day or how often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 
No, she didn't go every day, she couldn't very well. But she would go so many days. She used to go Pool Tuesdays by bus. Wash for the - preacher that was, Jago, have you ever heard tell of him, and she would wash for they. And then she used to go do
wn chapel house down Wesley, to Mr Isaac the station master of Camborne, of course father worked on the railway. But - that's - that's the only places she had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Jago the preacher, what was his occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Well he was schoolmaster over Pool. He haven't long had a daughter died - married Luke you up there, up Mount Pleasant.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Do you know whether she was paid very much for that kind of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 No, they didn't used to have more than about a shilling or eighteen}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8526680\charrsid3556460  }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 pence they days. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Would they sometimes pay in kind? Like give something to take home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 No, never used to have nothing like that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 This was after grandma came to live with you, would grandma look after you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Well see the days that mother went work when she gone 
out - she - she would look after us. Get dinner for us you know, when we come home from school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 You were saying when you had meals you were too busy eating to talk, you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Were you ever allowed to talk or were there no rules at all about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 No, didn't used to have no rules like that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 You simply got on with it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 That's right. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Did you have to ask to leave when you'd finished or would you just get up and go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 No, when we finish and wanted to get up and go out we'd go you see. Go out play then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 
I read about the other day a lady who said that when her little brothers and sisters were big enough to leave like the bottle, she remembers seeing her mother softening the food for the little child t
o start with by chewing it a bit herself, did you ever see that done?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 
Taste it or herself you mean, before give it to the baby, yes, she's done that - to make sure it's not too hot for him. I - used to do that for my children too. Yes, to make sure i
t wasn't too hot for 'em, taste it first you know. Not chew it up, because that wouldn't be right. Yes, it wasn't too hot, I gave it to him with a spoon. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 You wouldn't ever do that to soften it, like soften a crust or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Well, you see, when you give them bread and milk that's already soft isn't it, the - soaked in the milk, boiled milk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 That would be the next stage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Yes, I used to give my children - bread and milk a lot. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 After the bottle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 How soon would they go to solids then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 
Oh well didn't used to give them solid food not for - quite a while because - it hurt their stomachs we used to think, they days people were very particular with their children. Yes. Wouldn't go out and leave them no}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8526680\charrsid3556460  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 how on - without anybody there with them. Those days. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Do you remember what happened when the younger members of the family were born, when you were a bigger girl? Did you know about the birth?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 No, but - you used to have them very often by night, 
and we didn't know 'til the morning, we'd get out - of bed that mother had had the baby, you never heard no sound nor nothing. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 You don't remember what happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 No, didn't used to know anything. 'Cos you see - neighbour used to come in with her and - everything was quiet.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 You don't remember any being born in the daytime and you sent out to play or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 No. No, I can't remember any of those.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Did you know about childbirth before you had your children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Mother didn't tell you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 No, never - no, never knew anything. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 You had to learn by experience?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 
Yes, well - I - when I lived with my husband's mother for a little while, she used to say, you got to be bad before better, that's all I never knew. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 That's when you were carrying your children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Yes, didn't have - children didn't know then like they're told now, they're taught different now aren't they. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 So you didn't really know until the baby came what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 
When we were talking about family discipline, you said that there wasn't much punishment but father and mother didn't like you to come in late.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Well you see, we - we had to get in such a time you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Do you remember what time you had to get in of a summer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 
Well used to be nine o'clock because we had to get out in the morning and go to school see, and we used to play in the back - lane, and - we only had come around the corner see out in the next Centenary Row, that's where we lived,
 so - we used to try and manage to get it in time, we didn't want no hiding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 You would have a hiding if you were a bit late?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Oh, if we's late, yes. But father's mother, she lived with us, she would get behind the door where our father was still 
waiting for us, and jump between. We used to laugh about that, tell about that for years and years after.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 What would happen if father go there first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Oh we should have had a hit with this }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8526680\charrsid3556460 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460  belt}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8526680\charrsid3556460  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 he had round his waist. Used -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Just a strap across the back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Yes, and run up over stairs we would. 'Cos we only had a short passage you know from the door to the stairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 What about wintertime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Oh we didn't go out - play wintertime late, dark - dark see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Do you remember any of the games you used to play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Well no, we used to - sit down and read you know and - do our sums what we do at school. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 When you were out playing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Oh well - chase each - hide and seek and chase each other and - used to do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 I asked you if you ever collected anything, did you ever collect like broken china, did you ever collect anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 No. No. Well we used to have they all up in the garden you know, pieces thrown out that was broken. And then if we play shop we wou
ld have - those to - sell in a way, it was china.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Pretend?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Yes. Well we'd pick them up in the gardens and then the other children'd come with us to play would bring some too see. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 You all had your own little bits, you called them sherds didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 
Yes, that's sherds those days. Yes, didn't say china, sherds. And years ago they same clome, not china, clome. Mm. Yes, wash up the clome. Funny things don't it happen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 You didn't collect anything else, flowers or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 
No. Well - up in the garden you know there were - some weeds grow up with a - orange coloured flower on top, something like a daisy, we might pick a bit of that and put in - a tin or something for pretend they were flower selling, but no proper flow
ers. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 What about after you left school, was there any special time you had to be in then when you went to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 No. Glad to be in early then for getting out in the morning see, 'cos you used to have to go work early. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Father didn't lay down any time then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 
No. Sundays we didn't used to get up so early, though I used to get out very well because - I used to - teach up the Sunday school and - belong in the choir so I had to go in the morning, half past nine, used to go to school, S
unday school, and then I used to teach there and then from there we'd go in chapel for the service. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Any other members of the family teach in Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 No. No, I just - seemed to me I had the lead of everything. They never took to it way - choirs like I did. Funny wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Perhaps they didn't have the same voice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Well, no. And they - they weren't interested in it, not like I was, I always was interested in singing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 What about Maud, was she interested?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Oh she would 
sing. But - and she would play the organ, American organ, she could go down fair, and hear those old tunes on the organ, you know the hobby horses going around, she'd come home and play they all. Yes. Very - we used to have a lot of sing-songs with the fa
mily home. And then mother see was a good singer, she had a lovely soprano voice, I turned after her I expect. But I used to sing contralto but she was soprano.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Did mother go and sing in the choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 She - used to sing in a choir be}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8526680\charrsid3556460 f}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 ore she was married, in Redruth she was, she lived - she was from in there see. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Did she go to chapel when you were a girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Yes. Yes, they used go chapel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Mother and father?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Yes. We always had to go chapel and Sunday school. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Did mother wear her black cloak to chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Well yes, they days all - a bonnet, a bonnet. Black bonnet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Did she always dress in black?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Yes. And people used to wear bonnet those days, women. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Did they wear shoes or boots in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Well some used to wear boots and some used to wear shoes see. All depends what they could afford, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 The boots were very fine weren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Oh they used be fashionable boots did those days. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Buttons sometimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Well in summertime you want bit - something - not so hot didn't see around here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Was grace ever said at home before meals, did mother or father anybody say grace at all when you had your meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 No. Never used to do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Did your children say prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 
No, never used to - we - we might do it on our own but we wasn't taught to you know because - mother didn't - we did - she never had much time see for - when she'd get we all bed and - she had other work to do after that. Plenty of work with a f
amily isn't there. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Some of you would say prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Yes. You see, a lot - lot of girls make a lot of wash didn't they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 At Christmas time you told me that you used to save up any bits of money and all put together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Did you each have a present?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 No, we never used to have no presents, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 That would go on a bit of fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 
Yes, that would go on the - and - nuts and coconut and few oranges, we always had bit like that 'cos our money - we used to go shop with moth
er see, then - that night, Christmas Eve, always had - saved up our own money, we shouldn't have nothing we didn't do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Would you hang up your stocking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Well - sometimes we have, not very much. Too many to - yes, yes. That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Do you remember if you had a special dinner for Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 
Well used to have - sometimes you'd have a fowl, 'cos our - for a family a fowl in a pie was - most substantial wasn't it. And piece of beef or anything like that, we always had bit of something special.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Have any afters, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8526680\charrsid3556460 C}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 hristmas pudding or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Oh yes, mother used to make her pudding, yes. Can't say so rich as we do make them these days. But - but it was the pudding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Did any relatives call on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 No, no, d
idn't - didn't used to have no relatives come Christmas Day. It meant lot - cost didn't it. See had to study they things those days didn't they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Did you visit your relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Well no, we never - had a lot of - relatives for visit not then, see, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Father only had the one brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Well see that - yes -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Did mother have any brothers or sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 No. My mother had a sister, she we - was up London, married and up London, and she had a stepsister and she was over Ulster so we didn
't used to see none of they very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Did they ever come to see you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 
Well once upon a time the - the one up London might come home on a holiday in and out, not very often. They was - used to go to the Salvation Army officers up there they was. She and her husband.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Where would they stay if they came?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 
Well - used to come to our place. But see they didn't used to come not while we were all small see. 'Cos there wasn't a lot of difference in mother and her that - they wasn't - they all -
 they was had - had their children together like really. You can't travel when you've got they can you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 When they came how would you manage to sleep them then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Well see we - they used to keep - pay for their own food, we never used to have to - 
do none of them, well then we used to - go in a neighbours house sleep one or two of us you know to make room. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 This neighbour who didn't have any children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 That's right, and they had this - had the bedroom and - used to go in there see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Were you ever able to visit them, either in London or the other one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 
Well - I - I never could, 'cos see you couldn't go - on the railway free, not when you're fourteen. And - but they that was under - my - my youngest sister, Miss Gay, she went, 'co
s she wasn't so old as me see by ten years, and - she used to go up there when he have a weeks holiday they've gone up there for a week up London.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Would father have a special rate of fare because he worked on the railway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 No, worked - go free see, as weeks holiday free. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 He would take your young sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Did mother go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 And then see you couldn't go if you - after you got fourteen see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Would mother go as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Yes, mother and father would go. And take on
e or two children, and others we - what was old enough work would stay home, go work, see. 'Cos we had our granny there with us see. We use to always manage.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Not many children would get the chance to go to London from here would they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 No, I never had a chance to go. See, 'cos you - can't go - well with the railway after you was fourteen see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Did your mother's sister and her husband, was the Salvation Army their occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 The ones that were up London? Well see they used to belong on 
the Salvation Army, well see - they used to have to pay their own expenses to come down. Yes. And they didn't come see 'til their children were older and off work and then - that was a bit more money wasn't it for do it, and couldn't go not while they wer
e small.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 You said your parents voted Liberal, did they ever say why they thought that was the best?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 What was the best?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Liberal? Why did they think the Liberal policy was best?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Well people was always like that, they days, it was Conserv
ative and Liberal see, that's all there were running then, and of course - poorer class were all for - the Liberals, that was temperance wasn't it really, never used to - you - more or the better class would be Conservatives.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Would the Liberals mostly preach temperance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 
Well no, but we used to think, that was the temperance side see. Because s- the - Conservatives were counted - higher class people then than - than we were, yet they was quite a few people was Liberals those days. Used to have red
 and blue ribbon for Liberal and red, white and blue for Conservatives. I can remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Do you remember any families around here who you would term higher class who were Liberals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Well nearly all that we knew were Liberals. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Can you think of anybody special?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 No, was - was more Liberals than anything those days. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Was the Member of Parliament here as Liberal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Was the Member of Parliament Liberal here?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Yes, well there used to be - he used to be - I was going to tell you and couldn't - Coneybeare and Strauss, I can remember those.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Do you know which was which?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Coneybeare was Liberal and Strauss was Conservative. I can remember they. 'Cos we used to have the rosette red and blue see for - o
ur man. Red, white and blue for Conservative.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Do you know of anyone who had to vote Conservative because they were employed by a Conservative?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 No, no, I never heard tell of any.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Nor anybody who had to vote Conservative because their landlord was Conservative?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 No, never heard of anything, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 People could please themselves mostly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 When we talked before about how father's spare time interests, you said he belonged to the Philanthropic club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Yes. Club.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Where was that held?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 
Down - used to be down town - a room down there, I rather think - where the - Mining School is to now, but not - so - wasn't that big - that was newly built wasn't it that Mining School, isn't so old is it, but it was - used to 
be a room down there they used to have somewhere, behind, down there by the Mining School, he used to go down there to pay the club, once a month.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 So he used to play the club, what else did they do down there, did they have talks or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 No
, they - we - we used sometimes carry it and just drop the money in, they mark your card and we come away again. The head of the party I suppose had meetings together, we never used to go, not father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 What was the money for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Oh well see then whe
n you was - when you was home sick see you would have so much a week, something like insurance it is. Only they used to call it a club.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 It was done voluntarily?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Did father belong to any other clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Did he ever go out and have a pint at a pub occasionally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 No, never you see, never know him do that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Nor ever have a friend home for a drink or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Well not for - I think of a Saturday - he have gone out and had - of course he never ha
d the money, see we only had a shilling pocket money. Couldn't go far with that could he. But beer was tuppence a pint they days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 It was still quite a bit of your wages?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Would mother ever go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 No, mother never used to go nowhere, she had too much to do see. Was always mending and ironing and isn't it, work for family isn't it.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 When you used to take the money up to Basset Road school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 For the blankets.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Did you say that you took it for other people as well as your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Well - we - I have done but not very rare, 'cos most everybody used - go on their own you know, they had children they'd send those.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 It wouldn't be a little Saturday job you did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 They wouldn't give you a penny or ha'penny for doing it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 
No. I used to go - where mother was washing to and I - take her - her - have her money, she would have what she would have when she finish, I used to have that shilling, carry that up there. For my ticket.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 That was for your mother?
