iving. He would always come and if father was sick he would go to tell the other brother - to come up see him, he's sick.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 He cared?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Yes. Always looked - into the home you know. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 When the children were little were they affectionate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Yes. Yes.-
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Did people in those days think it was important to be affectionate to their children?
