\insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 mong - monger like Tyacks, and he worked there. And then he was took bad and died. And the other brother
, he was the barber here somewhere in Camborne. Johnnie he was called. Mm, so - I - they were - men when I was little, I can just remember the parents telling about them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Did you make any new friends when you went to work at the mill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Made frien
ds? Well, yes, there was two women there that were very nice, one was - like a - mother to me she was, she was years older, I - she was called Moyle and she lived Redruth. I - used to like her. And then there was another one called Roberts. I used to like
 her. But - they were two special ones if you will.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Did you make social friends of them, did you go places with them, outside your work?
