\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Well no, but they didn't live over here see, I lived Camborne and they used to live Redruth. And one lived C
arnkie, they was all around the work from different places, but - I - the ones I made friends with wasn't living over here see, I was the only girl I can remember going from Camborne over there. Can't remember no girls - I had one from Beacon used to work
 over there, woman, but she - no young ones. And then she didn't come my way see, she go across - railway to get Ltincroft.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 So you didn't have her company to come to and from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 No, I never had no company with they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 When you left school you went straight over there to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 
Well see - you had to - wait and get a job, you know, go see for a - place, and - then if you - they - thought you were suitable they would take you on. But I was the youngest was over there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 That was when you were fourteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 You didn't make any new friends because you left school, you continued with the same friends did you here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 No, I never used to - only these people what worked there you see. I never used to see - the people home in the Row 
where I lived, not more than Sunday, 'cos when I used to have to go work - half past six in the mornings was dark, and leave work five o'clock was dark when I got home again. See? Only when they stopped the working - why - 'til eight o'clock, went eight '
til five after a long time. But I never worked very long at eight o'clock, because I was married then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 You worked over there about five years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Yes, I was married two months before I was twenty. My father had to go down - Burrows used to take the 
- names and - for the banns put in, father had to go say he was willing for me be married we - I could put in the banns. They was particular they days. Mm. But anyhow - got through with all of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 You were saying about these two girls who had to carry the tin into the keeves, what extra was it you said they had to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 They used to attend the fuddles see, other }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8526680\charrsid3556460 f}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 uddles. They that carried the tin with the hand barrows see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 What happened to the tin in the hand barrows?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Jobs - that get go
od money, well they're better off aren't they, and some don't get so much, well they days was the same see. They had this place didn't they, if he's a manager in a mine he was - receiving good pay, he should be better off shouldn't he.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Was it possible for ordinary working class people to move up into a mining situation like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 
Well it all depends see if they were clever they'd work their way up. That's like my son was here just now, he was the boy packing like I did when I started. He foo - wh
en he finished - when he retired he was assistant manager. In the mill, not all the mine, just the mill where the tin was. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Some would go abroad?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Yes, go Africa, and - America, and then they would - do better for themselves, they used to go away to better theirselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Would some of the men get up into the managerial class if they went abroad?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Well they would - if work their way up you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Your account of your life after you were married and you had this lovely drive in a landau, was that usually done here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 
Yes. People used to always have - cabs they used to call them, and then they would - you could open them out see and they was called landaus then, that's mostly people had for weddings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Did the better off people do that as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Horses. Horses. Pardon? Oh yes, nearly - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Rather like they have a honeymoon now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Yes, that's right, yes, go for - used to go for a drive see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Can you remember how long that went on as a custom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 No, I - well mo
stly - you know, I expect it went on 'til - the motor cars come in - fashion see and then the horse and cabs was done away with mostly wasn't they then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 The guests who came to your wedding, would they all be family members?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Yes. Yes. It's - me s
isters and - me husband's brother's young lady, they was married a fortnight after - a fortnight after we. Mm. When they - well, see they took it down to the keeve first, and then they was - stirred up and packed, and after it was packed was carried in th
e tin house, in - with these here hand}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8526680\charrsid3556460 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 
barrows again. And then the men - two men used to be in there - one used to be out - cleaning out the keeve for they carry it in there and other two was in there bruising of it up. That's what they used to do.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Bruisin of it up, that was making it finer? Breaking it up was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Well, you - you was bruising it up, used to call it bruising up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 You remember we talked about whether there were any people that you used to call sir or madam, and you said that yo
u often called people sir or mister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 
Well - all depends who it was, you know, 'cos - some people used to call some people sir - and ordinary people they would call mister you know. Well - if we knew who they was - we would call them the same, see, Mr
 - were never allowed to call no man by their }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8526680\charrsid3556460 C}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 
hristian name, always had to say mister. Or sir. We weren't allowed to do that with our parents.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Did you call anybody master?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 No, mister we used to say mostly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Never heard the word maister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Yes, I've heard - my father used to say - maister. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 You were saying that they would call Mr Holman sir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 The Holman's, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 If you met them in the street how would you address them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Well, say Mr Holman 'cos I was used to them up 
- seeing them at chapel. But they might not know me from others see 'cos - it was - I didn't work foundry see, only see me in the chapel when he come. They used to come mornings more than anything at chapel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Would you say, good morning sir, if you met him, or good morning Mr Holman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Well - good morning Mr Holman, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Some families were rough and some respectable, can you recall any particularly rough families in this district?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Well no, I don't - think they was bad at all at that times, that I - they that I knew.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 You don't remember any really rough ones at all in this district?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Do you recall anybody referred to as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 What - the Holman's - I may - I told you that last time didn't I
, you know the Holmans, well they - had their foundry see and we used look up to they, thought they were - yes. There were others - people in the town too, my son said to me the other day - well, Albert - there was Captain Josiah Thomas, you ever heard te
ll of he have ee? Well I knew well, he used to preach up chapel. And then CV was a lawyer, his son, he was a preacher, I knew they, but I didn't used see they a lot see, only when they come preach.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 They were mine owners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Yes, they were mine - owners, yes. Dalcoath.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 That building where your father went for his philanthropic society is in memory of Captain Josiah Thomas isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Yes. Yes. Captain Josiah see was - manager of Dalcoath mine, well see - I wasn't very old when he was manager 
there, and I didn't know a lot about him see, only used go by hearing and hearing him preach. He was a lovely preacher. And his son used to preach up there too, he was a law - you know CV didn't ee?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Did they preach very long sermons in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Yes. Very long he used. Pity some wouldn't go hear 'em 'cos he preached too long. But we used to like him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 You enjoyed a long sermon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Oh yes, I did, I think he was lovely. We all - well he was good see, preacher and - he had a great voice on 
him lovely. Mm. If he was preaching now I should be able to hear him. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Would you consider they were a higher class than people round about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Well of course - of course they - was manager and the son was a lawyer, they were better off than we wasn't they. Should be.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Was it possible in those days for people to move up from one class to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Well it all depends what jobs you were in, see it is like now. Some people are in.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 You had a tea at home then did you after the drive?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 
Pardon? Oh yes, yes, come back - and have a - tea - at home then see. Mother would cook a meal for all when we come back. But after the wedding was in the morning you just have a snack - and then go for this drive you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Would any neighbours come in, or just the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Oh yes, some of the neighbours used to come in, the nearby ones you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Did they give presents in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Oh yes. I had a lot of presents. And I was in the choir, I had a present from the choir too see. Two of us was there in the choir. Yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Who else besides you, you and Maud was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Me and my - husband, we two were, in the choir, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 You were saying that after childbirth you yourself mother wouldn't allow you out for at least a month after your babies were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Oh no, I wasn't allowed to go out 'til after a month.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 That was for your own health's sake was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Yes, that's for your own health's sake, they - people were very particular those days. Nobody never used to go out very
 early after they had a baby.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Would they feel that the baby should be christened before you went out or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 No church service?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 No. No. My children were all christened but not - right away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 They had a ceremony in some parts of the country, they said a woman had to be churched after the baby was born.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 No. Mine were all - christened in a chapel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Can you remember at all how old the babies were when they gave up the bottle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 When they gave up -? No. Well - no, 
wasn't no particular age, when you - when - they would push them away theirselves when they didn't want them.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 They wouldn't be toddlers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Then - then we used to give them - drink then with a spoon you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Do you remember having to punish your children if they were naughty, or any special occasion when either of them was naughty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 No - one - nothing very particular with them see, not to be punished.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Sometimes it was when children began to toddle you know, if they got their hands into mischief. You don't remember anything of that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 
No. Well we - we used to be - learning them to walk off - you know, one from the to her, for make haste get them go off see, couldn't afford it - leave them too long without walking because - there w
as others to be attended wasn't it, and was glad when they could walk off. Mm. Ours wasn't bad for walking off early.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 At what age would they walk off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 I had one - one was late. One - a boy was late because he had rickets. He was two year and a h
alf before he walked off. But he was so in a race.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Which one was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 
Richard, the one down - Cranfield, but that one was - he was here just now, went off - he was - a year and two months I think when he walked off. Mm. He wasn't bad, nor Phyllis wasn't bad. But Richard was the last - latest one, 'cos he had rickets.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 How did they treat that then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Well I used to rub his - chins in olive oil, and my husband get - used to go down Cliff for bottle of sea water, we was told that was good.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 What would you do with it, rub it in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Yes. Yes, rub it in his chin.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 How old was he when he got better from that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Well he was two years and a half before he walked off properly, but we had a race made, he in the middle - and he would m
iles around with that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Sort of reins?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 
Yes, it used to be - you know - you know like a seat of the toilet, round, well it would be round, and then he would be legs, four legs, and wheels to the bottom of 'em, and he would push on that, he in the
 middle of 'em. And he walk - he learnt walk with that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 A sort of frame?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Yes. Like a frame. And he walked off by that. Mm. He was heavy too 'cos he was fat see - crawling around the floor see. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Bigger built that Alfred John?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Oh yes, he is now, great chap. You would think he was oldest look at him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Did you feel that there was any difference between craftsmen and labourers in those days? Did you ever see anything of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Crafty men?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Craftsmen like carpenters or fitters or tradesmen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 
Well see they learnt their trade and they used to do that work didn't they. But it's like other - everybody - had their trade didn't they, one used to do one thing and another another. That they didn't - that come quite natural didn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 No special social position would you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 
Yes. Yes. Some was painters - learnt painters and all like that didn't they. I had - right now is it - I had hard time - very hard times with shortage of - wages, and the family, and - the hard s
truggle, but with all of it, I got through, and I've done a lot of public work, and all free - serve I never done. I never charged anything - for all the singing that I done. I went free. The only - Ready? I always went free of charge for singing, the onl
y
 time I had - the choir master said he would give me a song, so I'd chosen - Lidels Abide With Me, and he bought that, that was the only time I ever had anything. I think that was a very good - deal. I was very pleased to have it and I well used the song.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Where did you sing it again, in chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 I used to sing it when I - we - we gave a concert I always sung that song.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 You must have known a good many singers in your time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Well there were a few you know going around. But Mrs Millar - and
 me used to go together, give concerts. We used to sing duets together, from the Tory Alexandra book, and Billy Graham's book, and - sometimes used to be a Mrs Roberts used to live down Park Road where I lived, we have gone together. Different ones you kn
ow.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Do you know any one particular soloist apart from your chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 
Well - down Wesley of course they had a quite a few, Ernie Olds, and Leslie Garveth tenor, and - there was - Mrs - I forget her name, she lived up Straparts, Beard, Mrs Beard was
 the soprano soloist, they used - and a Mrs Holman was the contralto soloist down Wesley choir.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Do you remember from the early days, before the end of the first world war, anyone who did well by singing, who made themselves better off?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Well, Ald
rovand Maynard from Illogan was a tenor soloist, he came - he was called the South African tenor because he came home from South Africa, but he used to be the special one home here. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 What was his occupation apart from singing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Well he didn't do anything at that time 'cos he came home from abroad you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Do you know anyone around here who were able to change their jobs or do better through their singing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 No, all used to come from the choirs you know round the town.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Do you remember any special performances that stand out in your mind from the early days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 
Oh well just - the ordinary singers you know from the choirs, and - they were good soloists and they used to go around give concerts you see. Mr Ernie Olds, he was a lovely
 bass singer, and Leslie Carveth was a lovely tenor singer, well they used to go and give concerts like they do down there now, choirs. But they were outstanding really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Did your singing bring you in touch with any other class of people than the working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Any choir - other choirs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Any other class of people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 
Oh yes, I used to - go different places then you fall in to know the people like wouldn't you, they would - come around you and I used to go to some places tea, with 'em. I was up Truto - St George's chapel singing with their women\rquote 
s choir from up Centenary, and went to different peoples place tea after the afternoon concert, and then we gave a concentration eight o'clock. Well I fell in you know with the organist and his wife, they were nice people, they were called Roberts too.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Did you go to any band functions in the early years of your marriage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Well I have gone to a lot of band concerts but - I used to get upset when he come for the judge get out, and they - then 
they didn't want me go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 
You said that apart from yourself and your sister Maud the other members of the family weren't so interested in music, did they have any special interests outside?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 No, never - didn't used - more than we do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Can you remember an special thing you did of a Christmas Day of an afternoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 
No, well - when I was young I could. Before I was married or thought of it - I can remember going out singing carols - with a - a little mission room choir, they formed so many s
ingers - and a man used to carry the harmonium around - two men used to carry the harmonium and we used to stop in the - street - I've been out Trelowarren Street four o'clock Christmas Day in the morning singing carols. Didn't used to go to bed they days
 
Christmas Eve. Then all days Christmas Day, my father used to follow us around, because my sister and me used to take up all the solos in the carols, and - she was sick one Christmas Day we were out and - we had to give up bit earlier than we should have.
 Mm. Something upset her stomach, but we too used to ding - do all the picking up of the solo work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Did you make collections?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Yes, but they used go around and collect, we used to get quite a bit of money. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 What would happen to that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 
Well sometimes we'd share it, sometimes it would go in the - go towards the mission upkeep, which was only like a dwelling house the place was, but no upstairs you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Where was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Up Centenary Row where I used to live.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 What was it used for normally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Only for the meetings. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Prayer meetings?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 
Yes, they had a choir there - and - the organist, he used to come in a - go in Centenary chapel in that choir in the mornings, sing in the choir. In the evenings he used to com
e in take we in the mission. Mm. Oh had lovely times, that used to be lovely services. Lovely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 What time of the day would that be then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Six o'clock in the evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Same time as the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 As chapel, yes. Yes. Same time. Of course it was really chapel services see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 You wouldn't be in the choir then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Not in the big choir, no, I went from that choir into the chapel, big choir. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 You started in the mission?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Who would normally preach in there then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Who would normally preach in the mission?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 
Oh well we used to have a - fellow called - John Brown, he was the tailor, he used to preach, and a - Mr Jenkin, they were so many of 'em, like a mission band you know, taking turns. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Did they sing any special kind of hymns?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Well the Sankey. All Sankey hymns. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 How long did that go on for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Oh went on for years but when I went in the chapel choir see I couldn't - attend in there then, somebody else took on there then. I u
sed to attend to the chapel choir see, practices and - concerts, well then I was married from in their see. From - Centenary choir. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 How long ago did that mission close down?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Oh - be - closed down before I was married. That's some years ago.
 'Cos see I had me golden wedding two years before me husband died, and he's been dead seventeen years eighteenth of May. That would have been nineteen years ago that was.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 So that mission hall would have been pulled down then would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 No, they got it for a workshop up there, the Rogers garage. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Before your marriage was it the custom to go for walks of a Sunday afternoon or evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Well - I - I didn't go far because I used teach the Sunday school. Then I had to go to school from t
wo to three. Then I used sometimes go down my - chap's mother's place to tea and then we come up go chapel, I never had time go far. I was kept busy they days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 You didn't have any favourite places for walking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Before your marriage did you have any special friends in the choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Oh well we were all friendly together you know, each one. Getting -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 No individual friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 No. No individual friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Going back to your days at home, was there any special time of the year that you had new clothes, like Christmas or Whitsun?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 
Oh used to have - only had new clothes Whitsun, for tea treats. When it was anniversary we'd have renovations, you know, anything we had would be renovated, a hat or anything, but didn't have new clothes so often as that, but Whitsun we had them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Would that be shoes and dress and everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Yes, new used to be then, dress and shoes and hat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 What about Christmas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Well just before Christmas, the cold weather, if we wanted a winters coat we've had it, but not nothing special else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Can you think of what in particular you would have brought your children up to consider important in life?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Well no, you see they went to the Sunday school and everyday school, and then soon as 
they was of any age they had to go work. See? And not one - none brought to no trade if you will. Of course we didn't call tin dressing trade 'cos that was all in your work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 What about ideals for life? Can you remember what you would have brought them
 up to consider was the best way of going on in life apart from there work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Oh they was always brought to respect theirselves all of them, and they never caused no trouble.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15611786 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 I suppose the chapel teaching would be the sort of ideals most people tried to live up to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2064242 MT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6842155\charrsid3556460 Yes. Yes.
